{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Storing a PASS review summary is blocked when any stored dimension finding for the same round has a FAIL verdict.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The real failure boundary is the wiring between summary write-path and persisted per-dimension findings scoped to the same round. A unit test over a pure validator can pass while repository/query scoping bugs still allow invalid PASS storage.","test_description":"Set up a real local test DB. Insert findings for round R with at least one FAIL and another round R+1 with all PASS. Attempt to persist a PASS summary for round R through the real service/repository path. Assert the write is rejected (or transaction rolled back) for R, while PASS storage for R+1 is allowed. This catches round-scoping and persistence-integration defects.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Stop-gate verdict computation reads per-dimension stored findings directly and does not rely only on hand-written summary text.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a cross-module data-source precedence bug: gate logic must read canonical stored findings, not summary text. Pure unit tests of gate helpers can miss repository wiring/config mistakes.","test_description":"Using the real gate service + local DB, store a summary text claiming all PASS and store at least one FAIL finding for the same round. Run stop-gate verdict computation through the production entrypoint. Assert verdict is non-PASS and evidence references stored findings, proving summary text alone cannot drive PASS.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Manual summary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an 